# Fixture: fm3-construct-bnode-per-row
# Finding: Failure Mode 3 — CONSTRUCT blank node scope per solution row
# Spec: SPARQL 1.1 §10.3
# Errata: SE-1 ("blank node in CONSTRUCT is local to each solution")
#
# Hypothesis: Each solution row in a CONSTRUCT result gets a *fresh* blank
# node for the template label _:b. The two triples within one row share the
# same blank node; across different rows the _:b label refers to *distinct*
# blank nodes. An implementation that uses a single global blank node for _:b
# across all rows merges all rows' generated triples onto one node — incorrect.
#
# Divergence: Parser / planner that shares blank-node identity globally
# across result rows produces a merged graph where row-1 and row-2 share
# the same blank node. Expected: one fresh blank node per template per row.
# Grammar-level behaviour: parses successfully.

CONSTRUCT {
  ?s <http://example/p> _:b .
  _:b <http://example/q> ?o .
}
WHERE {
  ?s <http://example/r> ?o .
}
